    <section>
      <title>Install from source</title>
      <para>VISHNU must be compiled with G++ (4.4.3 or greater) and CMake (2.8 or greater).</para>
      <para>Source tarball: vishnu_v1.2.4.tgz <ulink url="vishnu_v1.2.4.tgz">[download]</ulink> (added on 28th June 2011)</para>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Launch the VISHNU platform</title>
      <para>VISHNU is a distributed system and can therefore be installed on several systems as well as on a single system.
      When using several systems, the choice of which services to deploy on each system is dependent on the characteristics
      of the systems and of the network.</para>
      <para>Here is the list of processes that must be started to deploy all VISHNU services
        (see also the <quote>VISHNU Administrator's guide</quote> in the <link linkend="documentation">Documentation</link> section):</para>
      <orderedlist numeration="lowerroman">
        <listitem>
          <para>Database instance: either a MySQL or PostgreSQL database</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>CORBA OmniNames process (omniNames)</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>DIET Master agent process (dietAgent)</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>DIET LogCentral process (LogCentral)</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>All VISHNU SeD processes (umssed, tmssed, imssed, fmssed)</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </section>
